    "recap_headline": "Akron Athletics",
    "recap_text": "AKRON, Ohio -\nDown 10-2 going in to the bottom fo the fourth, the Akron baseball team scored 16 runs to take down the UMass Minutemen 18-17 on Sunday.\nHenry Hayman\nled the offense with four hits, which included a home run and three RBI.\nBrody Chrisman\nracked up three hits, three runs and two RBI.\nGabe Mathison\nrecorded two runs, two hits and four RBI against the Minutemen, while\nAtticus Huffstutler\nhad three hits in the win with one RBI.\nTaylor Bednar\n(1-2) picked up the victory out of the bullpen for Akron (9-10, 3-3). The right-hander went 4.2 innings, giving up five runs, all of them earned, on five hits, allowing three walks and striking out two.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nThe Zips scored in seven different innings on the way to the win. Akron broke a 10-10 tie and took the lead for good at 11-10 in the fifth inning on a Mathison walk from Brandon Wingenroth that scored Hayman.\nGAME NOTES\n\u00bb Hayman racked up four hits on the day for Akron.\n\u00bb Mathison drove in four runs for Akron.\n\u00bb Akron's highest scoring inning was the fourth, when it pushed seven runs across.\n\u00bb Four Zips had multiple hits in the ballgame.\n\u00bb Akron went 7-for-19 (.368) with runners in scoring position.\n\u00bb Akron pitchers faced 53 UMass hitters in the game, allowing 10 ground balls and seven fly balls while striking out eight.\n\u00bb The Zips drew 13 walks from UMass pitching.\n\u00bb Hayman led the Zips at the plate, going 4 for 6 with a home run and three RBIs.\nWHAT'S NEXT?\nAkron returns to Skeeles Field to battle Mercyhurst on Tuesday, March 17, for a 2 p.m. start."
